<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-25T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-25T11:00:00-05:00" n="756" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d756">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">834.01/5: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Howard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-25T12:00:00-04:00">February 25,
                                1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 25—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>27. The Minister for Foreign Affairs invited the Brazilian Chargé d’
                            Affaires, the British Chargé d’Affaires and myself separately and by
                            telephone to call at the Foreign Office today and tomorrow. The <pb facs="0964" n="865" xml:id="pg_865"/> Brazilian and I have declined
                            to go. I do not know what action will be taken by the British
                            representative who at the moment is not at his Legation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>